Definition.WordDefinition: Freud \Freud\ prop. n. Sigmund Freud, the founder of the practise of psychoanalysis. Born 1856, died 1939. [WordNet 1.5]
Freud n : Austrian neurologist who originated psychoanalysis (1856-1939) [syn: {Sigmund Freud}]
